OL,3,CMet Office confirms Thursday is the
OL,4,Chottest start to May on record
OL,6,FThe UK Met Office has confirmed
OL,7,FThursday May 1 to be the warmest start
OL,8,Fto May since records began.
OL,10,FWriting on X it confirmed temperatures
OL,11,Fof 28 degrees had been recorded at Kew
OL,12,Fgardens, beating the previous 1990
OL,13,Frecord of 27.4 degrees recorded in
OL,14,FLossiemouth.
OL,16,FThis is now the warmest May 1 since
OL,17,F1860.
