OL,3,CMet Office confirms Thursday is the
OL,4,Chottest start to May on record
OL,6,F"The fact is that, whilst adaptations
OL,7,Fcan be made to the way we live, a
OL,8,Frapidly changing climate is rapidly
OL,9,Fchanging the world as we know it; the
OL,10,Fnative wildlife and its habitat, the
OL,11,Fway that we produce the resources that
OL,12,Fwe need, the way the travel, the way
OL,13,Fwe care for the most vulnerable in our
OL,14,Fsociety - even, gradually, the
OL,15,Fphysical size of the island that we
OL,16,Flive on as rising sea levels threaten
OL,17,Four shores.
